WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.661 --> 00:00:03.161
(light music)

00:00:13.010 --> 00:00:15.370
- Your second trimester is a terrific time

00:00:15.370 --> 00:00:17.490
to start considering
which prenatal classes

00:00:17.490 --> 00:00:19.160
you would like to take.

00:00:19.160 --> 00:00:20.730
Preparing for the birth of your baby

00:00:20.730 --> 00:00:22.440
will help you feel more confident,

00:00:22.440 --> 00:00:24.020
both labor and delivery

00:00:24.020 --> 00:00:26.610
and caring for your baby subsequently.

00:00:26.610 --> 00:00:29.030
The classes we will discuss today include,

00:00:29.030 --> 00:00:33.140
hospital tours, childbirth
education and preparation,

00:00:33.140 --> 00:00:36.200
infant care, and breast feeding.

00:00:36.200 --> 00:00:38.490
Let's start with the hospital tour.

00:00:38.490 --> 00:00:40.440
We recommend that you tour the location

00:00:40.440 --> 00:00:41.930
where you plan to have your baby.

00:00:41.930 --> 00:00:43.820
See labor rooms makes it easier

00:00:43.820 --> 00:00:46.590
what it will be like to give birth.

00:00:46.590 --> 00:00:48.510
You will also feel more empowered to know

00:00:48.510 --> 00:00:50.930
where to go when the time comes.

00:00:50.930 --> 00:00:53.530
Ask questions such as,
where can we leave the car

00:00:53.530 --> 00:00:55.080
when we arrive in labor?

00:00:55.080 --> 00:00:57.630
Where do we check in, and does the baby

00:00:57.630 --> 00:01:00.219
stay in the room with me the entire time?

00:01:00.219 --> 00:01:03.670
It's important to feel
prepared for going into labor.

00:01:03.670 --> 00:01:06.020
Childbirth education
and preparation classes

00:01:06.020 --> 00:01:08.320
cover topics like, how
to know when you should

00:01:08.320 --> 00:01:10.820
go to the hospital for your delivery.

00:01:10.820 --> 00:01:12.750
These classes include strategies such

00:01:12.750 --> 00:01:14.607
as breathing exercises and positioning

00:01:14.607 --> 00:01:16.900
to help you cope with pain during early

00:01:16.900 --> 00:01:18.630
and active labor.

00:01:18.630 --> 00:01:20.730
It's helpful to ask questions such as,

00:01:20.730 --> 00:01:22.210
what can I do during early labor

00:01:22.210 --> 00:01:24.440
to help me copy with contractions, and,

00:01:24.440 --> 00:01:28.171
how can my partner best
support me through the process?

00:01:28.171 --> 00:01:31.020
Infant care classes
may include information

00:01:31.020 --> 00:01:33.580
about newborn care, infant CPR

00:01:33.580 --> 00:01:37.600
and information about newborn
immunization recommendations.

00:01:37.600 --> 00:01:39.620
You will learn about
recommended medications

00:01:39.620 --> 00:01:42.270
given to your baby during
the first few hours of life,

00:01:42.270 --> 00:01:44.493
and what kind of routine testing is done.

00:01:45.340 --> 00:01:47.880
Ask questions such as,
how can I best prepare

00:01:47.880 --> 00:01:49.800
for my baby's arrival at home?

00:01:49.800 --> 00:01:52.300
What information should
I bring to the hospital?

00:01:52.300 --> 00:01:54.580
What are key signs or
symptoms to watch for

00:01:54.580 --> 00:01:55.953
in my baby after birth?

00:01:57.140 --> 00:01:58.570
If you plan to breast feed,

00:01:58.570 --> 00:02:01.180
preparation is important for success.

00:02:01.180 --> 00:02:03.020
At a breast feeding
class you can learn about

00:02:03.020 --> 00:02:05.040
strategies for successful breast feeding.

00:02:05.040 --> 00:02:06.900
Get information about breast pumping

00:02:06.900 --> 00:02:08.580
when you need to be away from your baby,

00:02:08.580 --> 00:02:11.810
and connect with support
groups for after delivery.

00:02:11.810 --> 00:02:14.810
Questions to ask include,
who can provide support

00:02:14.810 --> 00:02:17.780
to me after delivery for
sustaining breast feeding?

00:02:17.780 --> 00:02:20.536
What kind of breast pump
is right for my situation?

00:02:20.536 --> 00:02:22.940
There are many classes available to cover

00:02:22.940 --> 00:02:24.380
these topics and more.

00:02:24.380 --> 00:02:26.780
Talk with your provider
to find out what options

00:02:26.780 --> 00:02:28.083
are available near you.

00:02:28.977 --> 00:02:31.560
(light music)

